definitions.definition: A pinniped ( Pinnipedia ), particularly an earless seal ( true seal ) or eared seal .
examples: The seals in the harbor looked better than they smelled.

main_definition: A pinniped ( Pinnipedia ), particularly an earless seal ( true seal ) or eared seal .

definitions.definition: A stamp used to impress a design on a soft substance such as wax.
An impression of such stamp on wax, paper or other material used for sealing.
A design or insignia usually associated with an organization or an official role.
examples: The front of the podium bore the presidential seal .

definitions.definition: Something which will be visibly damaged if a covering or container is opened, and which may or may not bear an official design.
examples: The result was declared invalid, as the seal on the meter had been broken.

definitions.definition: Confirmation or approval, or an indication of this.
examples: Her clothes always had her mom's seal of approval.

definitions.definition: Something designed to prevent liquids or gases from leaking through a joint.
examples: The canister is leaking. I think the main seal needs to be replaced.

definitions.definition: A tight closure, secure against leakage.
examples: Close the lid tightly to get a good seal .

definitions.definition: A chakra . (Can we add an example for this sense?)
